definition: son/child/seed/egg/small thing/1st earthly branch: 11 p.m.-1 a.m., midnight, 11th solar month (7th December to 5th January), year of the Rat/Viscount, fourth of five orders of nobility 五等爵位[wu3 deng3 jue2 wei4]/ancient Chinese compass point: 0° (north)

sentences.english: God really does change his people.
sentences.chinese: 神的確在改變他的子民。

sentences.english: Sons of Gondon, of Rohan, my brothers!
sentences.chinese: 剛鐸國和洛汗國的子民們，我的兄弟。

sentences.english: Christ expiated the sins and propitiated the divine wrath for all his people.
sentences.chinese: 基督替祂的子民贖了他們的罪，並且挽回了神的忿怒。

sentences.english: Balak the king of Moab summons Balaam to curse the people of God.
sentences.chinese: 摩押王巴勒命令巴蘭詛咒上帝的子民。

sentences.english: We all are shepherds to God's people first.
sentences.chinese: 牧人用敬拜的心，服事神國的子民。

sentences.english: We have taken on a task that will be difficult, but the people of the Empire are ready for the challenge.
sentences.chinese: 任重而道遠，但帝國的子民們已做好迎接挑戰的準備。

sentences.english: God told Ezekiel it was where his people that he loved were at.
sentences.chinese: 上帝告訴以西結，那是他喜悅的子民所居地。

sentences.english: God's people would go to war whenever he called on them.
sentences.chinese: 只要神一呼召，神的子民便會披甲上陣。

sentences.english: Now, promising salvation for his people, Kael'thas has returned.
sentences.chinese: 現在，向子民承諾了救贖的凱爾薩斯王子回來了。

sentences.english: As a people of God, we cannot and we should not have a divided heart.
sentences.chinese: 作爲主的子民，我們不能也不該心懷二意。

sentences.english: And all the multitude of the children of Israel going out from the presence of Moses.
sentences.chinese: 於是以色列子民全會衆離開梅瑟而去。

sentences.english: What can we do to make our church and ourselves people of grace?
sentences.chinese: 我們要如何才能令教會和自己成爲滿有恩典的子民呢？

sentences.english: And the children of Israel of the captivity kept the phase, on the fourteenth day of the first month.
sentences.chinese: 由充軍歸來的子民，於正月十四日，舉行了逾越節。

sentences.english: The Holy One of Israel must defend and deliver His own.
sentences.chinese: 以色列的聖者不能不保護拯救祂自己的子民。

sentences.english: May GOD have mercy on China and the Chinese, may your grace always be upon them. Shalom.
sentences.chinese: 願主保佑中國及其子民，願主常賜福與他們。

sentences.english: Laws are manifestations of asymmetries of power between the state and its subjects.
sentences.chinese: 法律是表現的不對稱性之間的權力對國家和其子民。

definition: to vow loyalty and devotion to
Han Chinese name for an ancient Central Asia country
